blogs.title: Web Development
blogs.shortDescription: Building websites using HTML, CSS, and JavaScript.
blogs.author: kajal123
blogs.readMore:
Web development is the process of creating websites and web applications.
It includes frontend development using HTML, CSS, and JavaScript, and backend
development using servers and databases.

Frontend focuses on user interface and user experience.
Backend handles logic, authentication, and data storage.
Modern web development also uses frameworks like React, Angular, and Vue.

blogs.title: Data Science
blogs.shortDescription: Learning from data to make better decisions.
blogs.author: Amit89
blogs.readMore:
Data science is the study of data to extract meaningful insights.
It combines statistics, programming, and domain knowledge.

Data scientists analyze large datasets to find patterns.
They use tools like Python, SQL, and machine learning models.
Businesses use data science for predictions and decision making.

blogs.title: Artificial Intelligence
blogs.shortDescription: Machines that can think and learn.
blogs.author: carezza23
blogs.readMore:
Artificial Intelligence allows machines to perform tasks that need human intelligence.
AI systems can learn from data and improve over time.

Examples include chatbots, recommendation systems, and self-driving cars.
AI is widely used in healthcare, finance, and education.

blogs.title: React Basics
blogs.author: Mocky67
blogs.readMore:
React is a JavaScript library for building user interfaces.
It uses components to create reusable UI elements.

React follows a virtual DOM for better performance.
It is widely used for single-page applications.

blogs.title: MERN Stack
blogs.shortDescription: Full-stack development using MongoDB, Express, React, and Node.
blogs.author: SaM001
blogs.readMore:
MERN stack is a full-stack JavaScript framework.
It includes MongoDB for database, Express for backend,
React for frontend, and Node.js for server.

MERN allows developers to build scalable web applications.
It uses JavaScript across the entire project.

blogs.title: Machine Learning Basics
blogs.shortDescription: Teaching machines to learn from data automatically.
blogs.author: Amit89
blogs.readMore:
Machine Learning is a branch of Artificial Intelligence.
It allows systems to learn from data without being explicitly programmed.

Machine learning models improve with experience.
Common examples include recommendation systems and spam filters.
Python is widely used for machine learning development.
